==English==

===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|flaxen}}, {{m|enm|flexon}}, {{m|enm|flexin}}, from {{inh|en|ang|fleaxen|t=of flax; flaxen}}, equivalent to {{af|en|flax|-en|id2=made of|t2=made of}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|en|/ˈflæk.sən/}}
* {{rhymes|en|æksən}}

===Adjective===
{{head|en|adjective}}

# Made of or resembling [[flax]] fibers.
#* ''The couple and their children have '''flaxen''' hair.''
# A pale yellow brown; the colour of dried flax stalks and of the fiber obtained therefrom.
#: {{color panel|C2B280}}

